{
  "message": "test(fr-sentinel): add fuzz_sentinel_parsers corpus + contract test\n\nFollow-up to dffd3ae: that commit landed only the incidental\nrustfmt fix to `crates/fr-sentinel/src/health.rs` because the\nsubstantive sentinel/lib.rs and corpus changes raced against\nanother agent's commit on the same files and dropped out of the\nfinal index. This commit lands the actually-substantive content.\n\n`crates/fr-sentinel/src/lib.rs`: new\n`fuzz_sentinel_parsers_corpus_matches_documented_contract` test\nthat walks `fuzz/corpus/fuzz_sentinel_parsers/`, runs every seed\nthrough `HelloMessage::parse`,\n`parse_replica_info_from_master`, and `parse_info_response` so\nthe parsers stay panic-free under the entire corpus, and pins\noracle expectations for the named seeds (sentinel/master ports\non `hello_valid_ipv4.txt`, two-replica master view on\n`info_master_replicas.txt`, partial-record skip on\n`info_replica_missing_ip_or_port.txt`, slave-down link state on\n`info_slave_down.txt`, and noisy-master tolerance on\n`info_noise_colons.txt`).\n\n`fuzz/corpus/fuzz_sentinel_parsers/`: 12 seeds covering valid\nHELLO messages (ipv4 + hostname), invalid HELLO shapes\n(non-numeric port, missing fields, extra fields), well-formed\nmaster INFO responses with one and two replicas, replica-side\nINFO with link up / down / bad numbers, an INFO with high repl\noffsets, and an INFO with extra colons + blank lines.\n\nPairs with the existing corpus + contract trio\n(`fuzz_config_file`, `fuzz_dump_restore`, `fuzz_acl_rules`) so\nthe sentinel parser surface gets the same fuzz + oracle\ntreatment as the other parser surfaces.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
